<br>
I wish to hold the follwing events:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE HTML START-->  <FONT size=3>The Great Fire Beetle Train</FONT><!--EZCODE HTML END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Who:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The No0bz.( Levels 1-8 )<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  What:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Attempting to train a fire beetle from &quot;the newbie log&quot; to the end of the trail near the EC zone line.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Where:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Nektulos Forest. Begins at &quot;the newbie log&quot;. Ends at the end of the trail near the EC zone line.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Why:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Cause Stone Cold Belmonte said so, and that's the bottom line.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Summary:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Fairly simple. No0bz each &quot;grab&quot; a fire beetle, and make a mad dash for the EC zone. The first person to &quot;train&quot; their Fire Beetle to the end of the path near the EC zone, wins.<br>
<br>
All contestants will be buffed, most likely by me (40 Cleric), so that even a level 1 player can compete in this event.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rules:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1) You may kill the other players' beetles, forcing them to run back to the newbie log to get a new one. Remember, they may also kill yours.<br>
<br>
2) You may &quot;steal&quot; another player's beetle(s) by engaging them in melee and taking the aggro. Remember, they may also &quot;steal&quot; yours.<br>
<br>
3) You may not impede the movement of another characters fire beetle in any fashion (ie Flash of Light, Fear, Root, etc.).<br>
<br>
4) At the start of the race, you may only have one fire beetle in tow. Thereafter, you may pick up as many as you like.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Prizes:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1st-50pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
2nd-25pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
3rd-15pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
4th-10pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
5th-5pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  <!--EZCODE HTML START-->  <FONT size=3>The Puntar Triathlon</FONT><!--EZCODE HTML END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Who:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> The No0bz (Levels 8-15)<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  What:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Running around N Ro in a triathlon of skill and stamina.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Where:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> N Ro. Begins and ends near Puntar Sandfisher's corpse <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Why:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Why not?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Summary:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Leg 1: Contestants run from Puntar, around pillar at Derv 3, back to Puntar.<br>
Leg 2: Contestants head into the water, swimming south along the shore, until they reach the dock to Velious, then turn around, and swim back to Puntar.<br>
Leg 3: Contestants drink 5-10 short beers (5 for levels 5-10, 10 for levels 10-15) to the platform. At the platform, players do 20 squat thrusts, then run around the solitary pillar near the shore, then back along the shore to the finish line (Puntar).<br>
<br>
All contestants will be buffed, most likely by me (40 cleric), so that in the event a contestant is aggroed, contestants should be able to survive until the next checkpoint, where a Midnight Council member will be waiting to help/instruct.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Rules</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1) Killing Puntar during the race will drop 30 seconds from your total time. So, if you kill Puntar and come in second place, you still may have a shot at winning.<br>
<br>
2) No speed modifying spells/items (ie SoW/JBoots) ar allowed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Prizes:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
1st-50pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
2nd-25pp+FS weapon of choice<br>
